# Multi-Dealer Architecture Restructuring

Royal Suzuky কে একটি সত্যিকারের multi-dealer platform এ রূপান্তর করা, যেখানে প্রতিটি Dealer এর service, sales, products, staff সব আলাদা থাকবে এবং Service Admin ও Sales Admin ডিলারের অধীনে থাকবে।

---

## Current State Analysis

### 🔴 Current Role Hierarchy (PROBLEM)

```
super_admin (1)          ← Platform owner
sell_showroom_admin (1)  ← ❌ Same level as super_admin!
sell_service_admin (1)   ← ❌ Same level as super_admin!
showroom_admin (2)       ← ❌ ABOVE dealer
service_admin (3)        ← ❌ ABOVE dealer
sales_admin (4)          ← ❌ ABOVE dealer
support (6)
accountant (7)
admin (7)
service_stuff (8)
sells_stuff (8)
dealer_owner (10)        ← Dealer is BELOW service_admin!
dealer (10)
dealer_manager (11)
dealer_staff (12)
sub_dealer (15)
technician (50)
customer (99)
```

> [!CAUTION]
> `service_admin` (level 3) and `sales_admin` (level 4) currently sit **ABOVE** `dealer_owner` (level 10). This means they are treated as "platform staff" — not as staff under a specific dealer. This is the fundamental problem we need to fix.

### Current Database Stats

| Item | Value |
|------|-------|
| Total models | 100+ |
| Dealers | 1 (Royal Suzuky Service Center) |
| Profiles | 4 (super_admin, service_admin, customer, null-role) |
| Tables with `dealer_id` | 50+ (most are already dealer-scoped ✅) |
| Tables **missing** `dealer_id` | 5 (needs fix 🔴) |

### Tables Missing `dealer_id`

| Table | Current State | Impact |
|-------|--------------|--------|
| `parts` | Global, no dealer scoping | Service parts should be per-dealer |
| `part_variants` | Global, no dealer scoping | Parts pricing per dealer |
| `special_tools` | Global, no dealer scoping | Tools per workshop |
| `service_packages` | Global, no dealer scoping | Service packages per dealer |
| `service_checklist_templates` | Global | Checklists per dealer |

### Tables Correctly Dealer-Scoped ✅

Products, brands, vendors, sales, service_staff, job_cards, service_appointments, service_invoices, service_estimates, warranty_claims, purchase_orders, inventory_batches, expenses, and 40+ more are already properly scoped with `dealer_id`.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Role Hierarchy Change** — `service_admin` and `sales_admin` will be moved **under** `dealer_owner`. This means they will NO LONGER have platform-wide access. They will only see data for their assigned dealer.

> [!WARNING]
> **Breaking Change** — If any existing code treats `service_admin` as a "platform admin" (level ≤ 8), that behavior will change. Service admins will now be dealer-scoped staff.

**Questions for you:**
1. `bike_models` — Should this remain **global** (all Suzuki models shared across dealers) or per-dealer?
2. `categories` — Should product categories be **global** or per-dealer?
3. Do you want a `sell_service_admin` and `sell_showroom_admin` role (combining sales+service/showroom)? Or just `service_admin` + `sales_admin`?

---

## Proposed Changes

### Proposed New Role Hierarchy

```
super_admin (1)          ← Platform owner (sees ALL dealers)
admin (5)                ← Platform admin  
─── DEALER BOUNDARY ─────────────────────────
dealer_owner (10)        ← Dealer owner (sees THEIR dealer only)
  ├── service_admin (11) ← Service wing head (under dealer)
  ├── sales_admin (11)   ← Sales wing head (under dealer)
  ├── showroom_admin (11)← Showroom head (under dealer)
  ├── accountant (12)    ← Finance staff (under dealer)
  ├── service_manager (13)
  ├── floor_supervisor (13)
  ├── service_stuff (14) ← Service floor staff
  ├── sells_stuff (14)   ← Sales floor staff
  ├── technician (15)    ← Technician
  └── dealer_staff (16)  ← General dealer staff
sub_dealer (20)
customer (99)
```

---

### Phase 1: Role Hierarchy — Database Migration

#### [MODIFY] Supabase `roles` table (SQL migration)

Update role levels in the database to reflect the new hierarchy:

```sql
-- Restructure role levels: move service/sales admins UNDER dealer
UPDATE roles SET level = 1 WHERE name = 'super_admin';
UPDATE roles SET level = 5 WHERE name = 'admin';
UPDATE roles SET level = 10 WHERE name = 'dealer_owner';
UPDATE roles SET level = 10 WHERE name = 'dealer';
UPDATE roles SET level = 11 WHERE name IN ('service_admin', 'sales_admin', 'showroom_admin');
UPDATE roles SET level = 11 WHERE name IN ('sell_service_admin', 'sell_showroom_admin');
UPDATE roles SET level = 12 WHERE name = 'accountant';
UPDATE roles SET level = 6 WHERE name = 'support';
UPDATE roles SET level = 11 WHERE name = 'dealer_manager';
UPDATE roles SET level = 13 WHERE name IN ('service_manager', 'floor_supervisor');
UPDATE roles SET level = 14 WHERE name IN ('service_stuff', 'sells_stuff');
UPDATE roles SET level = 15 WHERE name = 'technician';
UPDATE roles SET level = 16 WHERE name = 'dealer_staff';
UPDATE roles SET level = 20 WHERE name = 'sub_dealer';
UPDATE roles SET level = 99 WHERE name = 'customer';

-- Set role_type for dealer-scoped roles
UPDATE roles SET role_type = 'dealer' WHERE name IN (
    'dealer_owner', 'dealer', 'service_admin', 'sales_admin', 
    'showroom_admin', 'sell_service_admin', 'sell_showroom_admin',
    'accountant', 'service_manager', 'floor_supervisor',
    'service_stuff', 'sells_stuff', 'technician', 'dealer_staff',
    'dealer_manager', 'sub_dealer'
);
UPDATE roles SET role_type = 'platform' WHERE name IN ('super_admin', 'admin', 'support');
```

